{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"af0244bd-b3d7-4e10-8419-d125c3648cd0","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. **MSTest v3 requires at minimum .NET Framework 4.6.2, .NET Core 3.1, and .NET 5.0** — but there's a catch:\n\n- **`net5.0`** — End-of-life, but technically supported by MSTest v3.\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — End-of-life. MSTest v3.x **dropped support** for `netcoreapp3.1`.\n- **`net462`** — Supported ✅\n\n**Key issue:** You'll need to drop `netcoreapp3.1` (or upgrade it to `net6.0`+) before migrating to MSTest v3.\n\nAdditionally, MSTest v3 consolidates packages — you can replace both `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` with the single **`MSTest`** meta-package. There are also some behavioral breaking changes (stricter test class/method visibility rules, etc.).\n\n**Recommended steps:**\n1. Replace `netcoreapp3.1` with `net6.0` or `net8.0`\n2. Replace the two MSTest packages with `MSTest` version `3.x`\n3. Review any tests relying on non-public test classes/methods (v3 enforces `public`)\n\nWant me to make these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8e94a1a6-8de9-4b04-84b2-0248425f7a61","outputTokens":321,"requestId":"EC0B:214BB8:6566BB2:6DE3A1B:6A034C1A"},"id":"b6dc323f-787f-4c9a-9b52-92217a05769f","timestamp":"2026-05-12T15:49:58.947Z","parentId":"2a55f0ef-7e8a-46da-aa3a-b5c83adba1b0"}
